The paper discusses the use of AI techniques in autonomous systems and proposes a model checking based framework for planning and goal reasoning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on autonomous systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO (robotics) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of systematic methods for modeling and verification, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SE (software engineering) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the Goal Task Network (GTN) formulation, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SY (systems and control) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the proposed framework in the context of an experiment involving an autonomous underwater vehicle, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.PL (programming languages) sub-category.
